    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_v14axpuk">
            <alert>Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_za9n0wxb">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_pg1tumek">
                    <p xml:id="auto_dn3szxud">Provide pre-made pyramid models with labelled dimensions.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_9pm7tpir">
                    <p xml:id="auto_9qiltcja">Use pyramids with simple whole-number dimensions for initial practice.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_08k2k1be">
                    <p xml:id="auto_0k9y8rb2">Pair struggling learners with confident problem solvers.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_rk7hw9rb">
                    <p xml:id="auto_uppaqyim">Break down the formula into steps: (1) Find base area, (2) Multiply by height, (3) Divide by 3.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_smp7zaa0">
                    <p xml:id="auto_rjfmd9tp">Provide a step-by-step calculation template.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_g9kierej">
            <alert>On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_gngp0t2y">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_zfd91a4a">
                    <p xml:id="auto_78no2wof">Complete all practice problems independently.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_k7c9himm">
                    <p xml:id="auto_xm30kbtc">Explain the difference between a pyramid and a prism to a peer.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_qvykpd4s">
                    <p xml:id="auto_q7img4we">Provide mixed practice with different base shapes.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_yqlddigj">
            <alert>Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_cn9fn781">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_8ynr83tk">
                    <p xml:id="auto_lhn8co3d">Derive the formula using the relationship with prisms.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_akqtvnlz">
                    <p xml:id="auto_62dsle5h">Explore real-world applications: Egyptian pyramids, Mayan pyramids, modern architecture.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_oyjfs24t">
                    <p xml:id="auto_h4yptg1a">Apply the concept to composite solids involving pyramids.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_p6u33x9a">
                    <p xml:id="auto_2szwxgjb">Solve optimisation problems: Given a fixed volume, what dimensions minimise the surface area?</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_auf6t9h2">
            <alert>Extension Activity — Egyptian Pyramid Investigation:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_utuwyaw7">
            Work in groups.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_mjygbk71">
            <ol markers="1.">
                <li xml:id="auto_hbm0ofod">
                    <p xml:id="auto_11im80us">Research the dimensions of the Great Pyramid of Giza (base side length approximately <m>230</m> m, original height approximately <m>146.5</m> m).</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_eyp5copz">
                    <p xml:id="auto_8kusa29a">Calculate the volume of the Great Pyramid using the pyramid formula.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_hyk1ay0k">
                    <p xml:id="auto_pp5vi6pm">If each stone block has a volume of <m>1 \; \text{m}^3</m>, estimate how many stone blocks were used.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_sntk8135">
                    <p xml:id="auto_kv0kzr6u">Research how long it took to build the pyramid and estimate how many blocks were placed per day.</p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_4pdryqnp">
                    <p xml:id="auto_dk3qg1r0">Compare the volume of the Great Pyramid with modern buildings or structures.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </axiom>

